tourBios.curYearHigh: Played in four Web.com Tour events, all in August. Made three cuts with two top-25 finishes, a T18 at the Utah Championship and a T23 the following week at the Digital Ally Open.
tourBios.carHigh:
Has not played in a PGA TOUR event. 

2014: Made just one Web.com Tour appearance, missing the cut at the BMW Charity Pro-Am in May.

2013: Played in 18 Web.com Tour events, making nine cuts. Had three top 25s, with a T10 at the News Sentinel Open in August his best performance.

2012: Played on a Major Medical Exemption in 2013...Made the cut in just one of nine Web.com Tour starts. 

2011: Was T22 at the Chiquita Classic. Has three wins on the eGolf Tour and won that Tour's money title.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Four-time conference player of the year at Vance High School in Charlotte...Graduated cum laude at North Carolina-Charlotte...Four time All-American after winning five college events...Member of four conference championships in college.
tourBios.personal: Instructor is Scott Lefevre...Has two sisters Lauren and Lindsay...Never travels without his iPod. Always marks his ball with a 1988 quarter. Favorite Web sites are espn.com and charlotte49ers.com...Favorite pro teams are the Carolina Panthers, Charlotte Bobcats and the Golden State Warriors. Favorite movie is "Remember the Titans." Enjoys listening to Lil Wayne, Usher and Jay-Z...Favorite food is Chick-fil-A...Favorite athletes to watch are Kobe Bryant, Rory McIlroy, Tiger Woods and Rafael Nadal...Favorite gadget is his iPad and iPod...Favorite apps are Shazam and Pandora...Carries M&Ms and Goldfish crackers in his bag for snacks...Not many people know that he loves hip-hop music...Supports The First Tee of Charlotte.
